Luanda — A well-equipped centre for kidney diseases was inaugurated at Luanda's Main Military Hospital on Tuesday with promise to offer treatment to the staff of Angolan Armed Forces (FAA) suffering from disease. With capacity to assist 230 patients, the centre was inaugurated by the chief of Staff of the Angolan Armed Forces, Egídio Sousa Santos. The FAA general said the new dialysis unit will meet the major concerns related to the creation of specialised areas to provide a quality service to the patients. Dialysis services will also be extended to the family members of the staff of FAA, affected by the disease, he clarified.